{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add CI as a second Gerrit gate vote (`Verified`) via gerrit-to-platform ‚Üí GitHub Actions\n\n## Context\nThe v1 code gate (epics d251 infra + b744 code-review, both closed) uses a SINGLE\ndeterministic vote: the Gerrit `LLM-Review` label, cast by the review-bot's four-pass\nblocker. The intended end state requires BOTH (a) LLM review AND (b) CI (build / test /\nlint / typecheck) to pass. This epic adds the second, independent vote ‚Äî the Gerrit\n`Verified` label ‚Äî cast by CI.\n\n**This runs against the LIVE Gerrit-gatekeeper topology** (Gerrit owns `main`; GitHub is a\nlocked, read-only mirror). It is a **proof-of-concept** that mechanically proves the\nreview/signing/gate flow with a real, independent CI vote ‚Äî used by 1‚Äì2 developers on one\nproject, with agentic development producing frequent commits.\n\n### Decision log (2026-07-01 brainstorm ‚Äî grounded in prior art)\n- **Runner = GitHub Actions**, reusing the existing `.github/workflows/test.yml` checks. The\n  rebar GitHub repo is **public**, so Actions is free (incl. the macOS matrix cell) and the\n  run page is a **zero-auth, contributor-viewable log surface** ‚Äî satisfying the\n  \"clients can view logs\" requirement at no cost.\n- **Integration = adopt `gerrit-to-platform` (g2p) WHOLESALE**, the Linux Foundation\n  RelEng Gerrit‚ÜíGitHub-Actions bridge, exactly as ONAP / O-RAN-SC / OpenDaylight / FD.io\n  deploy it (~96 repos carry a `gerrit-verify.yaml`). This is the only mature, production-\n  proven pattern for this integration. A bespoke hybrid was **explicitly rejected** as a\n  Frankenstein that mirrors no real Gerrit deployment. (Jenkins+Checks and Zuul are equally\n  faithful patterns but presuppose a standing CI fleet whose value is multi-repo speculative\n  gating ‚Äî scale we do not have; both were rejected as over-weight for one repo.)\n- **The CI `Verified` vote is an authenticated Gerrit label vote** (service account over SSH),\n  NOT a per-vote HMAC attestation. The \"signing flow\" is already carried by the existing\n  attestation infra; this epic just adds the independent second gate vote.\n- **Two entailed posture changes accepted** (both are the g2p production standard; the\n  underlying ADRs are reconsiderable):\n  1. **Broaden Gerrit replication** to mirror `refs/*` (change refs) to the GitHub repo ‚Äî\n     a deliberate **reversal of ADR-0010** (main+tags-only mirror). `refs/changes/*` on the\n     mirror is how the runner fetches the patchset; `checkout-gerrit-change-action`'s\n     `gerrit-url` fallback covers replication lag. The mirror-lock ruleset still bars any\n     non-replication write to `main`.\n  2. **Inbound GitHub‚ÜíGerrit SSH vote path** ‚Äî a Gerrit service account whose private key is\n     a GitHub Actions secret; the workflow SSHes into Gerrit (port 29418) to cast `Verified`.\n\n## Locked design (the g2p production pattern)\n- **Trigger:** g2p Gerrit `hooks` (`patchset-created` / `comment-added` / `change-merged`)\n  `workflow_dispatch` a `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` with the nine `GERRIT_*`\n  inputs. (Single repo ‚Üí no org `.github` \"magic repo\"; a local, non-`required` workflow.)\n- **Workflow = fixed 3-job shape**, all actions SHA-pinned:\n  1. `clear-vote` ‚Üí `gerrit-review-action vote-type: clear` (resets `Verified‚Üí0`; the\n     GerriScary-safe reset), then a short `sleep` to allow replication.\n  2. `build-and-test` ‚Üí `checkout-gerrit-change-action` (fetch the exact `GERRIT_REFSPEC`)\n     then **our existing `test.yml` steps** (lint / typecheck / test matrix incl. macOS +\n     module-size / prompt-index / criteria-routing gates + coverage floor).\n  3. `vote` (`if: always()`) ‚Üí `im-open/workflow-conclusion` then `gerrit-review-action\n     vote-type: ${{ WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION }}` ‚Üí `Verified` +1 (success) / -1 (failure|cancelled),\n     with the **run URL in the vote message** (the log link).\n- **Gate:** new `[label \"Verified\"]` (NoBlock, ¬±1, `copyCondition = changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE`\n  mirroring `LLM-Review`'s strict reset) + `[submit-requirement \"Verified\"] submittableIf =\n  label:Verified=MAX`; voting restricted to Service Users. Submit now requires\n  `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND label:Verified=MAX AND -has:unresolved`.\n- **Re-run policy:** g2p `recheck` ChatOps (`comment-added` mapping `recheck ‚Üí verify`);\n  a new patchset auto-cancels the prior run (`concurrency: cancel-in-progress`).\n- **Fail-closed:** any dropped hook / failed run / crashed bridge yields no `+1` ‚áí no submit\n  (safe block, never a false pass).\n\n### GerriScary-safe non-negotiables (CVE-2025-1568)\nA carried/stale CI vote on an attacker's new patchset is a false-pass even when fail-closed.\nRequired, together: revision/patchset-scoped vote (the tested refspec) + `copyCondition` that\nresets `Verified` on any real code change + `clear-vote` reset at run start +\n`Verified` votable only by the CI service account + submit requirement keyed on the current\npatchset.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- A second, independent gate vote ‚Äî the Gerrit `Verified` label ‚Äî is cast by GitHub Actions\n  (via g2p) on every patchset.\n- The submit requirement requires BOTH votes: a change cannot submit unless LLM review passes\n  AND CI passes; the two are independent.\n- CI runs the SAME checks as `test.yml`, and contributors can view each run's logs (the public\n  Actions run page, linked from the vote).\n- The whole flow is proven end-to-end on the live Gerrit: red CI blocks submit; `recheck`\n  re-runs; a green change with both votes submits and replicates to GitHub `main`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **S1 ‚Äî Gate config** (`infra/gerrit/project.config`): add `[label \"Verified\"]` (NoBlock,\n      ¬±1, `copyCondition = changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE`) + `[submit-requirement \"Verified\"]\n      submittableIf = label:Verified=MAX`; grant the CI service account's group\n      `label-Verified -1..+1`; update the effective gate to require BOTH `LLM-Review=MAX` AND\n      `Verified=MAX` AND `-has:unresolved`.\n- [ ] **S2 ‚Äî Replication broadening** + superseding ADR: mirror `refs/*` (change refs) to the\n      GitHub repo; document the ADR-0010 reversal and confirm the mirror-lock ruleset still\n      bars non-replication writes to `main`.\n- [ ] **S3 ‚Äî g2p install** on the Gerrit host: enable the `hooks` (+ `replication`) plugins;\n      `pip install gerrit-to-platform` (Py‚â•3.11); symlink the three console-script hooks into\n      `$site/hooks/`; write `gerrit_to_platform.ini` (org PAT: Actions r/w, Contents+Metadata r)\n      + the `replication.config` symlink + the `recheck ‚Üí verify` mapping. Verify coexistence\n      with the existing review-bot webhook path.\n- [ ] **S4 ‚Äî Service account + credentials:** create a Gerrit service account + SSH key with the\n      `Verified` ACL; set GitHub repo vars `GERRIT_SERVER` / `GERRIT_SSH_USER` /\n      `GERRIT_KNOWN_HOSTS` / `GERRIT_URL` and secret `GERRIT_SSH_PRIVKEY`; document the inbound\n      SSH trust path + key blast-radius.\n- [ ] **S5 ‚Äî The workflow** `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`: the 3-job shape\n      (`clear-vote` ‚Üí `build-and-test` reusing `test.yml` steps via `checkout-gerrit-change-action`\n      ‚Üí `vote` off `WORKFLOW_CONCLUSION`), all actions SHA-pinned, run URL in the vote message.\n      Decide test.yml convergence (recommend the `gerrit-verify-manual-dispatch.yaml` hybrid so\n      one file serves Gerrit dispatch + manual/branch runs).\n- [ ] **S6 ‚Äî E2E proof + docs:** on the live Gerrit, prove a red CI blocks submit, `recheck`\n      re-runs, and a green change with both votes submits + replicates; update `CONTRIBUTING.md`\n      with the two-vote flow + `recheck`; capture design notes (cost / latency budget, flaky-test\n      handling, `copyCondition` re-run behavior). Record the change URL + both votes.\n\n## Decomposition\nSix stories (S1‚ÄìS6 above). S1 and S2 are independent config/infra; S3 depends on S2\n(replication) + the `hooks` plugin; S4 pairs with S3; S5 depends on S4 (credentials) and the\ngate (S1); S6 is the end-to-end proof gated on S1‚ÄìS5.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The `LLM-Review` vote itself (v1; epics d251 / b744).\n- Per-vote HMAC signing of the CI verdict (decided: authenticated label vote only).\n- Jenkins / Zuul self-hosted CI (rejected: over-weight for a single repo).\n- GitLab support in g2p (not yet available upstream).\n\n## Key references\n- g2p: github.com/lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform (README mandates `refs/*` full mirroring);\n  docs.releng.linuxfoundation.org/projects/gerrit-to-platform.\n- Real workflows: onap/.github + o-ran-sc/.github `gerrit-required-verify.yaml`; the annotated\n  single-repo template `lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform/examples/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml`.\n- Companion actions (SHA-pin): `lfreleng-actions/checkout-gerrit-change-action`,\n  `lfreleng-actions/gerrit-review-action`, `im-open/workflow-conclusion`.\n- GerriScary / CVE-2025-1568 (stale-vote supply-chain race) ‚Äî the copyCondition + reset rationale.\n- Local: `infra/gerrit/project.config`, `infra/gerrit/replication.config`, ADR-0007\n  (webhook receiver), ADR-0010 (replication), ADR-0013 (LLM-Review label), `.github/workflows/test.yml`.","title":"Add CI as a second Gerrit gate vote (Verified) via gerrit-to-platform -> GitHub Actions; require both LLM-Review and CI to pass"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782954300733666001,"uuid":"38d13f98-ae3f-4168-a69a-cca03aa4590e"}